Class Mood

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mood.jenaPlus.Mood
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Mood
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is the Mood class that instantiates a new Mood. A Mood object has all of the information needed about a mood. Created on 2017/2/25
    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Helen and Carlo

            java.lang.String userName)
        Instantiates a new Mood.
        Parameters:
        text - The trigger which will be < = 20 characters/<4 words
        addLocation - Boolean if a location is selected
        Latitude - the latitude
        Longitude - the longitude
        id - The mood icon ID
        social - The social situation of participant
        photo - Photo taken
        color - Color of the associated mood
        userName - the user name
